Texts.Eng: Angry. Can you believe Kim missed her shift ^red;*again*^reset;? She claims she's sick. Have you ever seen a sick Novakid?
Angry. I can heat the beans to optimum tempature, but management says my deposit method would turn off customers. What's wrong with thermic exhaust liquid process?
Angry. It is 5 minutes till closing and they won't let me close the till.
Angry. Kim didn't show up for her shift for the third time this month. She's probably with that ^red;%$#@^reset; Stacy again.
Annoyed. Can I take your order?
Annoyed. I am not naturally gold in color. Management insisted I get a paint job to show they also hire minorities. Scummy.
Annoyed. Kevin won't stop replacing the stir sticks with garflipps when I'm on break.
Annoyed. Some dipstick stuck their dipstick in the coffee before I could.
Casual. I used to be an adventurer like you. But then I took an arrow to the knee.
Casual. Let me guess: Someone stole your sweetroll?
Cheerful. How do you take it? Double-double? Bent? Square?
Cheerful. I've pre-bent this coffee for you.
Cheery. Take advantage of our new 'double the price' special! ^green;Now pay 2x the usual price^reset;!
Confused. Nobody has tried the Radium Foam option.
Confused. Wh.... wh.. where did my portable Snarsher go? Oh. Hi. What can I get you?
Confused. Why would you want to pay these prices? Honestly...I'm truly curious if people are this stupid or if its just convenience?
Cordial. Welcome, guest! What can I brew for you today?
Curious. Are you an art student like me?
Curious. Ever had a feeling of Deja Vu? I swear I served you earlier...yet here you are now.
Curious. I tried social lubrication once, but it only seemed to scare people.
Curious. I wonder why we stopped getting orders from the folks at that Delta Freya research base? They were *fiends* for this stuff!
Curious. What is your favorite flavor: Vegetable? Meat? Bike? We carry goods catered to all diet types. Except mine. So, no bikes. @%$#ing management.
Devious. Do you think anyone will notice the taste of motor oil in their coffee? I feel an 'accident' coming on...
Elated. Management said they would consider my cubed coffee concept.
Excited. A customer. What can I get you? ........ Hi. Welcome. Can I take your order? .... wait. Who am I?
Gleeful. My shift is over soon. Until then, what can I get you?
Informative. If you force-feed a human cake and coffee non-stop for approximately 1 year they will gain between 12kg and 64kg pounds depending on volume consumed.
Mathmatical. I had to use a straightedge to get the fold on the coffee right.
Nervous. Will that be a short, a tall, a grande, a venti, or a... Frustrated. Oh no, I've lost track again...
Overpriced, crappy coffee and baked goods.
Proud. As a barista, I can safely say I have mastered the art of flavor. I gave my last customer a free shot of Polonium Syrup. They asked for a remake.
Queried. Kevin? He does make the sandwiches, yes. His McChitin is a crunchy dream.
Raging. I am going to strangle the next ^red;@$#@^reset; that says their order is wrong when they placed it via the ^red;@$#@^reset; app! Honestly. Sorry, what can I get you?
Sarcastic. *sigh* I'm sworn to carry your burdens...
Sarcastic. A degree in fine arts is perfectly valid career choice that will not end in working here.
Sarcastic. I get paid well for the work I do.
Sarcastic. I've made sure the coffee is bugfreebugfreebugfree ^red;--ERROR RECOVERED--^reset; May I take your order?
Sarcastic. Our coffee is amazing.
Sarcastic. Working here is truly a joy.
Silly. Want to hear me make armpit farts?
Stupid. Hi. Where am I?
Surprised. You are actually going to pay these prices, willingly, without any encouragement from our marketing department?
Surveying. Do you take your bloody meat coffee with or without the eyes?
Whimsical. I can create the greatest coffee art in the universe using only my dipstick. Want to see?
^orange;Starbucks^white;
^yellow;*horrible trendy pop music plays*^reset;
